Q1. Why set the separate folder for the config node and the data node?

Q2. Are the log folder and the data folder in both the `confignode` folder and the `datanode` folder?

I guess your design of this folder structure is beneficial for starting the config node and data node in one distribution folder of one node.

> Q1. Why set the separate folder for the config node and the data node?

config node and data node have some sub directories or files with some names. Eg, data, logs, config/logback.xml... Separated folders are benefit to distinguish them.

> Q2. Are the log folder and the data folder in both the `confignode` folder and the `datanode` folder?

Yes, the log and the data folder can be separated by different node types.
